nDuration time.Duration\n40:   }\n41:   ```\n42: \n43: - [ ] **T012** Run `go build -o picod ./cmd/picod` to verify binary builds\n44: \n45: - [ ] **T013** Run `go vet ./cmd/picod/...` to verify no vet errors\n46: \n47: ### Phase 3: Create workload-manager (cmd/workload-manager/main.go)\n48: \n49: - [ ] **T020** Create `cmd/workload-manager/main.go` with:\n50:   - Package main\n51:   - Import statements:\n52:     - `flag`\n53:     - `os`\n54:     - `time`\n55:     - `k8s.io/klog/v2`\n56:     - `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager`\n57:   - Command-line flags:\n58:     - `--listen-address` (string, default: \":8080\")\n59:     - `--kubeconfig` (string, default: \"\")\n60:     - `--shutdown-timeout` (duration, default: 30s)\n61:     - `--enable-metrics` (bool, default: false)\n62:     - `--enable-logging` (bool, default: true)\n63:   - Initialize K8s client: `workloadmanager.NewK8sClient(kubeconfig)`\n64:   - Create workload manager: `workloadmanager.NewWorkloadManager(k8sClient.Clientset)`\n65:   - Create server: `workloadmanager.NewServer(config, workloadMgr)`\n66:   - Start server: `server.Start()`\n67: \n68: - [ ] **T021** Run `go build -o workload-manager ./cmd/workload-manager` to verify binary builds\n69: \n70: - [ ] **T022** Run `go vet ./cmd/workload-manager/...` to verify no vet errors\n71: \n72: ### Phase 4: Create router (cmd/router/main.go)\n73: \n74: - [ ] **T030** Create `cmd/router/main.go` with:\n75:   - Package main\n76:   - Import statements:\n77:     - `flag`\n78:     - `os`\n79:     - `time`\n80:     - `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/router`\n81:   - Command-line flags matching design:\n82:     - `--listen-address` (string, default: \":8080\")\n83:     - `--backend-timeout` (duration, default: 30s)\n84:     - `--idle-timeout` (duration, default: 60s)\n85:     - `--health-check-interval` (duration, default: 10s)\n86:     - `--health-check-timeout` (duration, default: 5s)\n87:     - `--max-conns-per-backend` (int, default: 100)\